<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>485340</id>
    <title>Private data being cleared on exit even though box is unchecked.</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.7) Gecko/2009021910 Firefox/3.0.7
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.7) Gecko/2009021910 Firefox/3.0.7</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">I always click "remember me" on relevant websites when I log in, and in Tools &gt; Options &gt; Privacy I have unchecked "Always clear my private data when I close Firefox".</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">However it appears that the cache is still being cleared every time I close Firefox, because every time I log in again, I'm signed out of everything and have to sign in all over again.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">1 Log into website, checking the 'remember me' box.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">2 Go to Tools &gt; Options &gt; Privacy and make sure "Always clear my private data when I close Firefox" is unchecked.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">3 Exit Firefox.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.5">4 Restart Firefox and find yourself logged out of everything again.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
Not cleared my cache so I can stay logged in to everything!</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
